USB Settings

Figure 7-17 USB

Table 7-9 USB Parameters

Field Name

Description

Make Device Non Bootable

The server can boot from a USB device.

Select Disabled, Enabled, or Platform Default.

Legacy USB Support

The system supports legacy USB devices.

Select Disabled, Enabled, or Platform Default.

USB System Idle Power Optimizing System

The USB System Idle Power Optimizing setting is used to reduce USB EHCI idle power consumption.

Depending upon requirement, select high-performance, lower-idle performance, or platform default.

USB Front Panel Access Lock

USB front panel lock is configured to enable or disable the front panel access to USB ports.

Select Disabled, Enabled, or Platform Default.

Port 60/64 Emulation

The system supports 60h/64h emulation for complete USB keyboard legacy support.

Select Disabled, Enabled, or Platform Default.

USB Port Front

The front panel USB devices are enabled or disabled.

Select Disabled, Enabled, or Platform Default.

USB Port Internal

The internal USB devices are enabled or disabled.

Select Disabled, Enabled, or Platform Default.

USB Port KVM

The KVM USB devices are enabled or disabled

Select Disabled, Enabled, or Platform Default.

USB Port Rear

The rear panel USB devices are enabled or disabled.

Select Disabled, Enabled, or Platform Default.

USB Port SD Card

The SD card drives are enabled or disabled.

Select Disabled, Enabled, or Platform Default.

USB Port vMedia

The virtual media devices are enabled or disabled.

Select Disabled, Enabled, or Platform Default.

All USB Devices

All physical and virtual USB devices are enabled or disabled.

Select Disabled, Enabled, or Platform Default.
